South Africa will dispose of a portion of its stake in Telkom with an option to buy it back later, finance minister Malusi Gigaba said in his budget speech on Wednesday.  Treasury is seeking to avoid breaching the expenditure ceiling due to bailouts of ailing state firms, Gigaba said. The government holds a stake of about 39% in landline provider Telkom. “The expenditure ceiling is threatened in the current year, as a result of government’s recapitalisation of South Africa Airways and the South African Post Office,” he said.  Read: More SOCs set to default To read finance minister Malusi Gigaba’s full medium-term budget speech, click here. 